Gazprom, Vekselberg May Need to Sell Power Units, Vedomosti Says

-- B y   Y u l i y a   F e d o r i n o v a
-- 
2011-12-05T04:47:55Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-12-05/gazprom-vekselberg-may-need-to-sell-power-units-vedomosti-says.html
OAO Gazprom  and billionaire Victor Vekselberg may merge their power assets only after selling part
of them,  Vedomosti  reported today, citing Vitaly Korolev,
director of the electricity sector department at the Federal
Antimonopoly Service.  Gazprom may need to sell the Pskov and Kirish stations in
 Russia ’s northwest, the newspaper said.  Vekselberg’s holding company may also need to sell two
thermal stations or reduce its ownership of TGK-6 and TGK-7 to
less than a controlling stake, Vedomosti reported.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Yuliya Fedorinova in Moscow at 
 yfedorinova@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
John Viljoen at 
 jviljoen@bloomberg.net  